# Azure Integration Services & Serverless - Interview Notes

## Event Grid vs Service Bus vs Event Hubs

| Feature             | Event Grid                      | Service Bus                      | Event Hubs                      |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------- | -------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| Purpose             | Event routing and notifications | Enterprise messaging             | High-throughput event streaming |
| Communication       | Push-based                      | Pull-based                       | Streaming ingestion             |
| Use Case            | Trigger reactions to events     | Reliable message processing      | Telemetry, logs, analytics      |
| Message Size        | Up to 64 KB (Basic)             | Up to 256 KB (Standard)          | Event streaming                 |
| Ordering            | No                              | Yes (FIFO with Sessions)         | Partition-based                 |
| Dead Letter Queue   | No                              | Yes                              | No                              |
| Duplicate Detection | No                              | Yes                              | No                              |
| Message Retention   | Event delivery retries          | Up to 7 days                     | Configurable retention          |
| Filters             | Subject/Event Type Filters      | SQL Filters, Correlation Filters | No                              |
| Typical Scenario    | Blob upload triggers Function   | Order processing workflow        | IoT telemetry ingestion         |

### Interview Question

**When would you choose Service Bus over Event Grid?**

Use **Service Bus** when:

* Message ordering is required.
* Guaranteed delivery is needed.
* Dead-lettering is required.
* Duplicate detection is needed.

Use **Event Grid** when:

* Event-driven architecture is needed.
* Lightweight notifications are sufficient.
* Multiple subscribers need event routing.

Use **Event Hubs** when:

* Millions of events per second need ingestion.
* Streaming analytics is required.
* Processing logs, telemetry, or IoT data.

