# Azure Functions

Azure Functions is a serverless compute service used to run event-driven code.

## Hosting Plans

### Consumption Plan

* Default timeout: 5 minutes
* Maximum timeout: 10 minutes
* Pay-per-execution
* Automatic scaling
* Cold starts possible

### Flex Consumption Plan

* Default timeout: 30 minutes
* Maximum timeout: Unlimited
* Reduced cold starts
* Event-driven scaling
* Always-ready instances available

### Premium Plan

* Default timeout: 30 minutes
* Maximum timeout: Unlimited
* Pre-warmed instances
* Reduced cold starts
* Automatic scale-out
* More memory and CPU

### Dedicated (App Service) Plan

* Default timeout: 30 minutes
* Maximum timeout: Unlimited
* Shared App Service resources
* Predictable billing

---

## HTTP Trigger Timeout

HTTP-triggered functions have a maximum request duration of **230 seconds** due to Azure Load Balancer timeout limitations.

